{"metadata":{"title":"Authentication","modules":[{"name":"Registry API"}],"role":"article","roleHeading":"Article"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.example.RegistryAPI\/documentation\/RegistryAPI"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how to authenticate with the Swift Package Registry API for accessing private packages and publishing."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Swift Package Registry API uses token-based authentication to secure access to private packages and privileged operations like publishing. This guide explains how to authenticate your requests."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"Obtaining an Authentication Token","anchor":"Obtaining-an-Authentication-Token","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To get an authentication token, you’ll typically use the login endpoint:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["\/\/ Create login request","let loginURL = URL(string: \"https:\/\/registry.example.com\/login\")!","var request = URLRequest(url: loginURL)","request.httpMethod = \"POST\"","request.setValue(\"application\/json\", forHTTPHeaderField: \"Content-Type\")","","\/\/ Set credentials - implementation depends on registry provider","let credentials = [\"username\": \"your-username\", \"password\": \"your-password\"]","request.httpBody = try JSONEncoder().encode(credentials)","","\/\/ Send request","let (data, response) = try await URLSession.shared.data(for: request)","","\/\/ Parse token from response","let tokenResponse = try JSONDecoder().decode(TokenResponse.self, from: data)","let authToken = tokenResponse.token"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"level":2,"text":"Using Authentication Tokens","anchor":"Using-Authentication-Tokens","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Once you have a token, include it in your reque